request.description:
*Store tokens already created externally with Elavon Converge so it can be used at a latter stage*

The request parameters are as follows:

*   **psp_reference**(required) - You can use "ssl_txn_id" from Converge's response;
*   **token_id**(required) - "ssl_token" from Converge's response with prefix **ID:**. For example if the **ssl_token** you receive from Converge is "987****1234" you need to pass "ID:987****1234" as **token_id**;
*   **card_expire_date**(required) - You can use "ssl_exp_date" from Converge's response;
*   **card_type**(required) - You can use "ssl_card_short_description" from Converge's response;
*   **holder_name**(optional) - You may use "ssl_last_name" and "ssl_first_name" to construct the name.


The **id** returned in the response may be used with [booking_credit_cards](https://api-docs.clock-software.com/#5c98293b-8a79-449f-b92b-a0d1efd70bb8) endpoint. Parameter **"credit_card_id"**

